


For performance testing:

Modify run.sh to run this command:

	rumprun -S xen -di xenevent.run


In the makefile, /comms_chan/rump_comms/rump-xenevent/apps/xenevent_app/ comment out the following line:

	CFLAGS += -DMYDEBUG


The last thing to do is to modify xenevent_common.h in the libxenevent directory

	In the following code snippit found around line 56

#ifdef MYDEBUG
#  define DEBUG_BREAK()                                                 \
    DEBUG_PREAMBLE();                                                   \
    bmk_printf ( "At breakpoint\n" );                                   \
    asm("int $3\n\t")
#else
#  define DEBUG_BREAK() ((void)0)
#endif

	On the line:
	
		bmk_printf ( "At breakpoint\n" );
	
	Comment out the “\” at the end of the line.

	Then completely comment out the line: 
	
		asm("int $3\n\t")

from command rumprun -S xen -dip -D1234 xenevent.run
remove p, -d 1234 to get rumprun -S xen -di xenevent.run

Makefile in xenevent_app directory 

remove -ggdb from CFLAGS variable

Makefile in Libxenevent directory
#CPPFLAGS += -DMYDEBUG
